{      Howard's Corner      }
^-|CP||fp|2|ht|f|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There are 2 different ways to play what the cue bids mean in Unusual Over Unusual.

Method A - the lower cue bid shows the lower of the two remaining suits, the higher cue bid shows the higher of the two remaining suits. For example, over  both 1H-2N and 1S-2N, 3C shows hearts and 3D shows spades. 

Method B - the lower cue bid shows support for opener's suit and the higher cue bid shows the other remaining suit. For example, over 1H-2N, 3C shows hearts and 3D shows spades, but over 1S-2N, 3C shows spades and 3D shows hearts.

You and your partner must agree as to which method you use.|
